Flight Control Surface Actuator - Detailed Inspection

ATA Chapter (Illustrative): 27 — Flight Controls
S1000D DMC (Illustrative and Generic): XXXXXX-A-27-31-01-00A-710A-A
Aircraft/Company: Not Specified / Generic Manufacturer


This task involves:

    - Gaining access to the specified flight control surface actuator.
    - Cleaning the actuator and surrounding area to facilitate inspection.
    - Performing detailed visual checks for:
        - Corrosion, pitting, or flaking on the actuator body, rod, and end fittings.
        - Cracks, dents, or physical damage to the actuator housing and mounting points.
        - Condition and security of hydraulic lines, fittings, and electrical connectors.
        - Evidence of hydraulic fluid leakage from seals, lines, or the actuator body.
        - Security of all attachment hardware (bolts, nuts, cotter pins).
        - Condition of protective finishes and markings.
    - Performing dimensional checks (if specified by engineering sources) for rod extension play or bushing wear using appropriate measuring tools.
    - Checking for proper lubrication at pivot points.
    - Recording all findings and discrepancies.


