Key Authoring Considerations
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
 Factor                                   |   Importance
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Flight Control Safety                    |   Ensure flight controls are safetied/deactivated and tagged out per AMM general procedures before starting work. 
                                          |   Accidental movement can cause severe injury or damage.
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Hydraulic System Pressure                |   Verify hydraulic system pressure is OFF and residual pressure is bled before disturbing 
                                          |   any hydraulic connections (even for visual checks near fittings).
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Access & Lighting                        |   Adequate access to all parts of the actuator and sufficient lighting 
                                          |   (including use of inspection lamps/mirrors) are critical for a thorough inspection.
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Cleanliness                              |   The actuator and surrounding area must be thoroughly cleaned to reveal small defects like cracks or early corrosion.
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Inspection Criteria Definition           |   Clearly define what constitutes "acceptable" vs. "unacceptable" for each inspection check 
                                          |   (e.g., "no visible cracks," "corrosion not exceeding X depth/area").
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Use of Inspection Tools                  |   Specify correct use of any required tools like mirrors, magnifying glasses, borescopes 
                                          |   (if internal inspection is required), or dimensional measurement tools.
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Damage Classification/Reporting          |   Procedures for classifying and reporting any found discrepancies 
                                          |   (e.g., to maintenance control, engineering liaison) must be clear.
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________
 Corrosion Prevention                     |   If protective coatings are disturbed, specify requirements for touch-up.
__________________________________________|_______________________________________________________________________________


